18:51.315 --> 18:54.359
and... to be honest, you
know, my heart is still there.

18:55.077 --> 18:57.884
So I see you're running Gnome.

18:58.200 --> 19:01.228
You know, I'm actually on KDE myself.

19:01.229 --> 19:04.335
I know this desktop environment
is supposed to be better but...

19:04.932 --> 19:06.324
you know what they say.

19:06.325 --> 19:10.437
- Old habits... they die hard.
- An executive running Linux with...

19:10.438 --> 19:12.109
Yeah, I know what you're thinking.

19:12.110 --> 19:14.198
I'm an executive. I mean...

19:14.199 --> 19:16.193
why am I even running Linux?

19:16.906 --> 19:19.199
Again... old habits.

19:21.899 --> 19:24.459
It's gonna be fun working with you.

19:24.999 --> 19:27.999
I should join the rest of the group.

19:28.000 --> 19:30.999
Bonsoir, Elliot.

19:36.699 --> 19:39.699
Sometimes I dream of saving the world.

19:42.999 --> 19:46.222
Saving everyone from the invisible hand,

19:46.223 --> 19:48.999
one that brands us with an employee badge.

19:51.999 --> 19:55.035
The one that forces us to work for them...

19:56.272 --> 19:59.921
The one that controls us every
day without us knowing it.

20:01.550 --> 20:03.999
But I can't stop it.

20:04.000 --> 20:05.999
I'm not that special.

20:07.999 --> 20:09.999
I'm just anonymous.

20:10.000 --> 20:11.999
I'm just alone.

20:15.566 --> 20:17.788
If it weren't for Qwerty,

20:17.789 --> 20:19.999
I'd be completely empty.

20:25.999 --> 20:29.252
I hate when I can't hold in my loneliness.

20:31.137 --> 20:32.734
This crying has been happening too often,

20:32.735 --> 20:34.827
every other week now.

20:38.699 --> 20:41.699
What do normal people do
when they get this sad?

20:43.999 --> 20:45.999
They reach out to friends
or family, I think.

20:49.999 --> 20:51.999
That's not an option.

20:54.999 --> 20:57.999
I do morphine.

20:58.000 --> 21:00.844
The key to doing morphine
without turning into a junkie

21:00.845 --> 21:03.725
is to limit yourself
to 30 milligrams a day.

21:03.726 --> 21:04.973
Anything more

21:04.974 --> 21:07.899
just builds up your tolerance.

21:07.900 --> 21:10.999
I check every pill I get for purity.

21:11.689 --> 21:13.999
I have 8 milligram Suboxone for maintenance

21:14.000 --> 21:15.999
in case I go through withdrawals.

21:16.000 --> 21:18.999
Shit! I'm out again.

21:22.374 --> 21:26.293
- How much?
- On the house.

21:26.594 --> 21:29.699
No, Shayla. Not doing that.

21:29.700 --> 21:32.299
Okay? This is just a regular drug deal

21:32.300 --> 21:34.299
- like it always is.
- Fine.

21:34.800 --> 21:36.034
So what are you you to tonight?

21:36.035 --> 21:37.999
'Cause I tried to post
something on your Facebook

21:38.000 --> 21:39.659
and couldn't find you.

21:39.700 --> 21:41.527
I'm not on Facebook.

21:41.528 --> 21:45.139
- What? Why not?
- 'Cause I hate Facebook.

21:48.000 --> 21:49.999
That's crazy.

21:51.260 --> 21:54.679
Well... you want to do these together then?

21:55.102 --> 21:57.700
Pure Molly...

22:10.699 --> 22:13.330
Don't ever make decisions
when you're on morphine.

22:24.399 --> 22:27.399
Instagram check-in for
Krista at Pierre Loti.

22:27.400 --> 22:29.013
Okay, Michael Hansen.

22:29.014 --> 22:31.457
Time to find out who you really are.

23:19.399 --> 23:21.399
- Thank you. Bye.
- Bye.

23:24.220 --> 23:26.299
Taxi!

23:30.299 --> 23:35.299
Uh, hi... I just left my
keys in one of your cabs.

23:35.300 --> 23:37.299
56Y2.

23:38.599 --> 23:39.599
Sure.

23:42.699 --> 23:44.699
What about you two? Huh?

23:45.299 --> 23:47.299
You guys got any spare change?

23:47.899 --> 23:49.698
Help me out?

23:49.699 --> 23:51.899
New York's expensive, guys. Come on.

23:53.235 --> 23:55.999
306 Hawthorne. Thank you. Thank you.

24:18.700 --> 24:20.500
Come on, asshole. Piss already.

24:20.501 --> 24:22.080
Come on!

24:22.081 --> 24:23.699
Come on! Will you... will you go?

24:23.700 --> 24:24.925
- Come on, go, go!
- Hey!

24:25.226 --> 24:26.513
Go, will ya?

24:26.514 --> 24:28.000
Hey.

24:31.718 --> 24:32.999
May I borrow your phone?

24:33.000 --> 24:35.999
Mine's dead. I need to call my mom.

24:42.399 --> 24:44.399
Thank you.

25:04.499 --> 25:06.499
No answer. Thanks anyway.

25:23.671 --> 25:27.873
- Angela, is everything okay?
- I need you to come to AllSafe.

25:28.499 --> 25:30.173
You're there? It's 3:00 in the morning.

25:30.174 --> 25:33.259
They attacked Evil Corp servers
again, but it's bad this time.

25:33.260 --> 25:34.100
It's a DDoS attack.

25:35.099 --> 25:37.877
- Did you call Lloyd? He's on call.
- Yeah, he's here.

25:38.596 --> 25:42.684
- Is he talking to their tech department?
- He's online with them, but so far nothing.

25:44.399 --> 25:47.131
I don't think that Lloyd can handle this.

25:48.199 --> 25:49.902
Look, Gideon just put me on this account.

25:49.903 --> 25:51.572
I can't screw up in my first week.

25:51.573 --> 25:54.199
I need you. Please.

25:55.699 --> 25:57.441
I'll be right there.

26:08.299 --> 26:11.207
- Finally!
- Calm down... it's only been an hour.

26:11.208 --> 26:16.026
Yeah, well, an hour in Evil Corp time is
like $13 million in revenue, approximately.

26:16.027 --> 26:17.661
Actually, I calculated that.

26:17.662 --> 26:19.673
That's exactly how much they lost.

26:19.955 --> 26:21.926
Don't worry. I got you.

26:22.862 --> 26:24.299
Lloyd, what's up?

26:24.300 --> 26:26.299
Lloyd!

26:26.799 --> 26:29.386
Elliot. This is bad.

26:29.387 --> 26:30.968
Worst DDoS attack I've ever seen.

26:30.969 --> 26:33.541
- Did you reconfigure the DNS?
- Yes!

26:33.542 --> 26:35.783
- Stop the services.
- I already stopped the services,

26:35.784 --> 26:38.160
tries to reboot the servers
but they're not coming back up.

26:38.399 --> 26:41.415
Dude, someone is straight up fingerblasting
their entire network right now.

26:58.613 --> 27:01.082
They just started reporting on the outage.

27:08.799 --> 27:11.575
Shit. This is worse than I
thought. They're in the network?

27:11.576 --> 27:13.518
What's the status update?

27:13.519 --> 27:16.023
He's here. I thought we
set up security protocols

27:16.024 --> 27:19.419
so that this doesn't happen.

27:19.744 --> 27:21.788
- Where's the attack coming from?
- Everywhere, obviously.

27:21.789 --> 27:25.210
- The USA, Finland, Thailand, Kuwait...
- Start restarting the services, load sharing,

27:25.211 --> 27:27.348
redirect the traffic.
Call Prolexic for help.

27:27.968 --> 27:31.634
- Wait. What?
- I don't think this is just a DDoS attack.

27:33.599 --> 27:36.046
I think they got a rootkit
sitting inside the servers.

27:36.372 --> 27:38.927
- What's a rootkit?
- It's like a crazy serial

27:38.928 --> 27:40.399
rapist with a very big dick.

27:40.803 --> 27:44.387
- Jesus, Lloyd.
- Sorry. It's malicious code that completely

27:44.388 --> 27:46.961
takes over their system.
It can delete system files

27:46.962 --> 27:49.494
and stop programs. Viruses, worms...

27:49.495 --> 27:51.202
- How do we stop it?
- That's the thing.

27:51.203 --> 27:53.345
It's fundamentally
invisible... you can't stop it.

27:53.346 --> 27:54.719
All of their servers are timing out.

27:54.720 --> 27:56.034
None of them are coming back up.

27:56.299 --> 27:58.143
That's because every
time we restart the server

27:58.144 --> 28:00.105
the virus replicates itself during boot up

28:00.106 --> 28:01.242
and crashes the host.

28:01.243 --> 28:02.410
_

28:02.631 --> 28:04.282
How are we supposed to bring up the network

28:04.283 --> 28:08.084
- if we can't restart the servers?
- We can't.

28:09.001 --> 28:11.299
Which is what they wanted.

28:11.586 --> 28:14.791
By defending ourselves, we ended
up spreading the virus everywhere.

28:15.859 --> 28:16.998
Only thing we can do

28:16.999 --> 28:19.299
is we've gotta take the
whole system offline,

28:19.300 --> 28:22.328
wipe the infected servers
clean, then bring them back up.

28:24.884 --> 28:26.299
You're coming with me.

28:26.300 --> 28:28.274
- Yeah.
- Lloyd.

28:28.275 --> 28:30.502
Tell everybody to start
taking everything offline.

28:30.503 --> 28:33.220
- On it.
- Uh, the server farm in Dulles.

28:33.221 --> 28:34.824
We're gonna need the jet.

28:49.300 --> 28:51.145
They're booting the network back up.

28:51.146 --> 28:52.967
Now, you're downloading
the logs, right because...

28:52.968 --> 28:54.909
- Stop. Tell him to stop.
- What?

28:54.910 --> 28:57.199
Don't start the boot
sequence. You guys missed one.

28:57.200 --> 28:59.964
There's an infected server up and running.

29:00.899 --> 29:02.899
What's the ETA before it hits this server?

29:08.599 --> 29:10.599
The backup server up and running?

29:10.600 --> 29:13.373
It's ready, but it's not
configured for auto switch.

29:19.104 --> 29:21.805
We need to redirect the
traffic, need to switch DNS.

29:25.399 --> 29:27.861
You got this, you got this, you got this.

29:29.515 --> 29:32.452
- This is impossible.
- You got this, you got this, you got this.

29:33.074 --> 29:35.423
It's almost at the back server!

29:43.749 --> 29:45.400
We still up?

29:52.222 --> 29:55.894
We're okay.

29:56.099 --> 29:59.137
Yeah.

30:07.116 --> 30:08.725
Hank.

30:08.726 --> 30:10.527
I'm gonna take a look at
the infected server, okay?

30:10.528 --> 30:14.806
- Give me a minute.
- Yeah. Uh... I'll meet you at the elevators.

30:21.072 --> 30:22.835
They must have left a mark or something.

30:22.836 --> 30:24.752
Every hacker loves attention.

30:24.753 --> 30:27.479
They don't just do DDoS
attacks for no reason.

30:33.821 --> 30:36.626
This is it. Fsociety.

30:37.099 --> 30:39.099
Is that supposed to be a joke?

30:39.100 --> 30:42.471
This was way too easy. They
didn't hide it well at all.

30:44.431 --> 30:46.083
_

30:46.958 --> 30:49.189
_

30:50.033 --> 30:52.485
This note is for me.

30:53.499 --> 30:55.885
They're telling me to leave it here.

30:55.886 --> 30:59.152
But why? Doesn't matter.

30:59.153 --> 31:01.376
Time to shut them down.

31:04.991 --> 31:06.568
Why can't I delete it?

31:06.569 --> 31:09.081
I don't want to delete
it. I want it to stay.

31:09.082 --> 31:11.299
What's wrong with me?

31:18.300 --> 31:20.735
I'll reconfigure the
access to the root directory

31:20.736 --> 31:23.957
so only I can use it. And no one will know.

31:28.299 --> 31:29.702
For you, sir.

31:35.480 --> 31:40.302
- Did you know that I'm gay?
- Uh...

31:43.499 --> 31:46.331
- No.
- Hmm.

31:49.199 --> 31:53.199
Consider this me coming
out to you then, okay?

31:53.799 --> 31:55.799
It's hard because I don't
like to talk about my sex life.

31:55.800 --> 31:59.799
But my partner, he gets very paranoid.

31:59.800 --> 32:02.799
He thinks I'm ashamed of...

32:02.800 --> 32:05.799
He wants me to be more public about it, so,

32:05.800 --> 32:08.799
Anyway, I'm gay.

32:12.499 --> 32:14.499
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

32:20.099 --> 32:24.007
Hey, man, don't worry about it.

32:24.320 --> 32:26.099
Hackers have a short attention span.

32:26.100 --> 32:28.829
They'll get bored, harass someone else.

32:28.830 --> 32:33.899
Evil Corp is thinking about leaving us.

32:33.900 --> 32:37.036
And I don't know if I can blame them.

32:38.899 --> 32:41.733
They could have called
their other security teams.

32:41.734 --> 32:43.684
- Mm.
- They called you.

32:44.899 --> 32:46.800
Well, somebody over there likes us,

32:46.801 --> 32:49.736
but Terry Colby, he's getting the pressure.

32:49.737 --> 32:53.722
And he calls the shots.

32:53.723 --> 32:56.899
Evil Corp is 80% of our business.

32:56.900 --> 32:59.899
If we lose them, it's gonna be it for us.

32:59.900 --> 33:02.805
It's gonna be it...

33:03.000 --> 33:04.899
For me.

33:13.352 --> 33:15.502
I feel like I can talk to you.

33:17.199 --> 33:19.845
I mean, more than the others, anyway.

33:20.899 --> 33:25.298
I'm sure, in a weird way,
you'll be happy if we went under.

33:25.999 --> 33:28.480
Oh, come on. Come on.

33:29.699 --> 33:32.573
I know you hate wearing
those stupid shirts.

33:41.899 --> 33:43.899
Gideon?

33:46.099 --> 33:49.099
I promise I'll find them.

34:01.900 --> 34:04.874
Evil Corp service should
be back up soon enough.

34:04.875 --> 34:07.855
I'll take a look at the dat
file. I'll ask my IRC contacts

34:07.856 --> 34:09.649
about fsociety when I get home.

34:09.650 --> 34:11.706
I've never seen their
name on the boards though.

34:11.706 --> 34:13.899
They've gotta be new, but they're good.

34:20.899 --> 34:22.899
Rough night?

34:28.899 --> 34:30.518
I'm getting off here.

34:31.699 --> 34:33.699
I think you should come with me.

34:33.900 --> 34:36.899
But only if you didn't delete it.

34:36.900 --> 34:40.472
You deleted it, we got
nothing to talk about.

34:40.899 --> 34:43.761
Are you talking to me?

34:46.199 --> 34:50.150
Stand clear of the closing doors, please.

35:02.699 --> 35:07.529
- Who are you?
- We gotta wait for the Q.

35:14.899 --> 35:18.919
- Then what?
- Then we're going to Brooklyn.

35:18.920 --> 35:21.735
Out by Coney Island.

35:22.140 --> 35:23.575
Why?

35:24.248 --> 35:28.425
What's there?

35:28.899 --> 35:32.899
Obviously you're gonna
ask a lot of questions.

35:32.900 --> 35:35.873
It's weird what you're
doing right now, I get it.

35:37.799 --> 35:40.799
I... I can't tell you
anything until we get there.

35:48.999 --> 35:51.013
Can't smoke in here.

35:55.699 --> 35:57.785
You've been following me.

35:58.786 --> 36:00.553
Why?

36:02.699 --> 36:05.699
What do you want from me?

36:09.699 --> 36:12.699
My dad was a petty thief.

36:12.700 --> 36:14.699
Never could hold down a job.

36:14.700 --> 36:17.953
So, he just robbed,
convenience stores, shops,

36:17.954 --> 36:20.023
small-time stuff.

36:20.699 --> 36:23.549
One time, he sat me down, he
told me something I never forgot.

36:23.699 --> 36:28.411
He said, "Everyone steals.
That's how it works.

36:28.412 --> 36:32.545
You think people out there are
getting exactly what they deserve? No.

36:32.546 --> 36:34.699
They're getting paid over or under,

36:34.700 --> 36:38.088
but someone in the chain
always gets bamboozled.

36:40.295 --> 36:44.699
I steal, son, but I don't get caught.

36:44.700 --> 36:47.699
That's my contract with society.

36:47.700 --> 36:49.699
Now if you can catch me
stealing, I'll go to jail.

36:49.700 --> 36:54.396
But if you can't, then
I've earned the money."

36:58.108 --> 37:00.418
I respected that, man.

37:02.699 --> 37:06.935
I thought that shit was
cool as a little kid.

37:10.296 --> 37:12.699
A few years after that,

37:12.700 --> 37:15.699
they finally caught him.

37:15.700 --> 37:17.764
Sent him to jail.

37:17.765 --> 37:21.975
Dies five years later.
My respect goes with him.

37:24.699 --> 37:28.556
I thought he was free doing
what he did, but he wasn't.

37:30.153 --> 37:32.365
He was in prison.

37:33.699 --> 37:36.551
Just like you are now, Elliot.

37:38.699 --> 37:41.699
But I'm gonna break you out.

38:37.881 --> 38:43.532
- Why would you guys actually meet IRL?
- You remember that hacker group O-Megz?

38:43.533 --> 38:45.374
They got outed by their
own leader to the FBI,

38:45.375 --> 38:47.067
and six hackers went to prison for it?

38:47.068 --> 38:48.530
You know how they got 'em?

38:48.531 --> 38:50.095
They went on the dude's computer,

38:50.096 --> 38:55.713
tracked 'em all down through emails,
VPN sessions, chat messages, texts.

38:55.714 --> 38:57.699
One guy, and the whole thing comes down.

38:57.700 --> 38:59.819
- It's what's called...
- A central point of failure.

38:59.820 --> 39:03.185
Right. Because they
refused to meet in person,

39:03.186 --> 39:07.141
they compromised each other every time
they sent so much as a smiley face.

39:07.142 --> 39:11.764
The rule here is, it's
done here, and only here.

39:13.699 --> 39:17.102
It ends when you walk out that
door, and begins when you walk in.

39:17.103 --> 39:21.141
Our encryption is the real world.

39:21.699 --> 39:24.762
- How do you talk to each other then?
- We don't.

39:24.763 --> 39:27.683
We come and go, work on
the project when we can.

39:28.699 --> 39:30.699
- How do you trust them?
- I give them an exercise.

39:32.700 --> 39:35.691
If they pass, they join us.

39:35.899 --> 39:38.584
- If they fail...
- The DDoS attack last night,

39:40.249 --> 39:42.469
you were testing me.

39:49.284 --> 39:51.418
You said there was a project.

39:51.829 --> 39:54.966
- What's the project?
- That'll come later.

39:54.967 --> 39:57.328
I just wanted you to see the place.

40:02.999 --> 40:05.999
There's not much you can do without a CPU.

40:10.999 --> 40:12.356
I'm crazy.

40:12.357 --> 40:14.999
I have to be crazy because
that didn't just happen, right?

40:15.000 --> 40:19.013
This is a delusion. Is this a
delusion? Shit, I'm a schizo.

40:20.999 --> 40:24.073
Have I really lost it this time?
No, no. Last night happened.

40:24.074 --> 40:26.438
It was real. Angela called
me. I was at AllSafe.

40:26.439 --> 40:27.999
Evil Corp's servers were compromised.

40:28.000 --> 40:29.999
Those are facts, not delusions.

40:30.000 --> 40:32.608
I know. I know, I know I
realize I'm saying all of this

40:32.609 --> 40:36.057
to an imaginary person, but I created you.

40:36.058 --> 40:38.493
I didn't create this.

40:38.999 --> 40:41.181
Oh, thank God you're here.

40:41.182 --> 40:43.827
I was just about to go
wait in the Starbucks.

40:44.599 --> 40:46.182
You live in a bad neighborhood.

40:46.183 --> 40:48.836
- Do you know that?
- I do know that.

40:49.399 --> 40:54.149
Do you want to get high and
watch your favorite movie?

40:54.999 --> 40:58.611
Oh, you saved our asses last night. I
thought Gideon was definitely gonna fire me.

40:59.999 --> 41:01.129
Where have you been?

41:01.130 --> 41:06.972
- I thought you'd be sleeping.
- I... yeah, I fell asleep on the train.

41:08.799 --> 41:11.564
That sounds like such a lie,

41:12.799 --> 41:15.770
but, whatever. I don't want
to get into that right now.

41:16.071 --> 41:18.154
So you want to do this?

41:23.499 --> 41:26.839
I miss Qwerty. I hope she still loves me.

41:34.799 --> 41:36.799
Shit.

41:36.800 --> 41:38.972
She wasn't supposed to be here, okay?

41:38.973 --> 41:42.031
- Give me a minute and I'll get rid of her.
- That's okay.

41:42.032 --> 41:45.951
Um... This is great.

41:46.701 --> 41:48.997
- Elliot, I'm happy for you.
- No, it's not like that.

41:48.998 --> 41:53.540
Well, maybe it should be, you
know? It's good that you're...

41:55.699 --> 41:57.564
dating.

42:00.599 --> 42:02.133
Well, I'll see you on Monday.

42:02.599 --> 42:04.599
We can do movie night next time.

42:05.280 --> 42:08.317
- I promise, okay?
- Yeah.

42:15.099 --> 42:17.006
Have fun.

42:29.599 --> 42:33.375
Mm, Elliot?

42:33.991 --> 42:38.772
Oh, shit. Is it Wednesday?

42:38.773 --> 42:41.840
- Shayla.
- I have to move my car.

42:41.841 --> 42:45.757
Shayla, leave.

42:48.116 --> 42:49.599
Now.

42:52.952 --> 42:54.770
No mention of Mr. Robot anywhere.

42:54.771 --> 42:56.599
No mention of fsociety.

42:56.600 --> 42:58.116
Not on any of the hacker boards.

42:58.117 --> 43:02.011
Not on IRC, forums, blogs,
no one's heard of them.

43:05.914 --> 43:09.979
Property was owned by Fun Society
Amusement, LLC for 13 years.

43:10.499 --> 43:12.839
Owner was shot a killed
a year and a half ago.

43:12.840 --> 43:14.315
No owner since.

43:14.616 --> 43:17.999
And the ownership history before
that is sparse to nonexistent.

43:18.399 --> 43:21.533
This guy is good. Very good.

43:26.909 --> 43:31.135
Doesn't matter. Their arcade
network's IP is in the DAT file.

43:34.599 --> 43:37.409
